{
  "stem": "12462.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The tribunal-- very-- President Lawrence said, after I had been going maybe 15 minutes, Captain Sprecher, we understand from what you have said that the defendant, von Schirach, clearly was the main leader of Hitler Youth, and that he made a lot of statements of the kind that you have said, and we think that you've adequately presented that point, subject to the defense responding.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And please go on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I still had some material I wanted to get in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I tried to bring some more in, and he shut me up again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I then said, would your honors be interested in hearing of the relationship between Baldur von Schirach as head of the youth leader and the-- and Himmler, who was the head of the SS?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was asking the court, do you want to hear this evidence, which I've got?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Which was kind of a funny question.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And everybody, after a while, said you-- you little bastard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said, well, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I haven't seen it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually, the document book had-- in English containing this document was already in front of him, but he hadn't gotten to it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was a-- a document where Schirach had talked very strongly about the Jews, and about the superiority of the Nordic race, and things like this.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he'd then made an arrangement with Himmler, the head of the SS, that, at a certain stage, Himmler had the right to select some people from the Hitler Youth and put them into special programs, so that they would be-- become members of the SS.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So this was kind of a pulling out-- from the Nazi point of view-- kind of an elite group and pushing them into the SS.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was very strong evidence.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
